section.section:
Of the 13 members:
3 shall be members of the Maryland Association of the Deaf;
2 shall be mental health practitioners who are hearing impaired individuals;
2 shall be mental health practitioners who are not hearing impaired individuals;
2 shall be individuals in the field of deaf education;
1 shall be a parent of a hearing impaired individual;
1 shall be from the Maryland Association for Hearing Impaired Children; and
2 shall be public members who represent the community at large.

The Secretary shall appoint the advisory committee from recommendations made by:
The Maryland Association of the Deaf;
The National Association of the Deaf;
The International Association of Parents of the Deaf;
The Maryland School for the Deaf;
The Alexander Graham Bell Association of the Deaf;
The Maryland Regional Council of Child Psychiatry;
The Maryland Chapter of the National Association of Social Workers;
The Maryland Psychological Association; and
The State Department of Education.
